# llm-tts-api — request examples
#
# This file is in VS Code REST Client / JetBrains HTTP Client format.
# Install the "REST Client" extension (humao.rest-client) in VS Code, then
# click "Send Request" above any `###` block. The server must be running
# (see README "Quick Start"). Adjust @baseUrl if you bound a non-default port.
#
# Cycle-2 surface covered below (post-HF-2 + post-HF-3):
#   * Audio presets (fast / balanced / quality, plus precedence demo).
#   * Voice-cloning roundtrip via the voice store (POST → use → DELETE).
#   * OpenAI-compatible /v1/audio/speech (uses TTS_DEFAULT_PRESET).
#   * Liveness/readiness + catalog probes.
#
# Out of scope: postproc tuning (S-031), wav24/flac end-to-end (S-033),
# quality-stream downgrade (S-032). Those surfaces will land in S-036.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000

###############################################################################
# Health & liveness (FR-HL-01, FR-HL-02)
###############################################################################

### Liveness — lock-free; always 200 once the ASGI worker is up.
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### Readiness — 200 only after warmup + seed ingestion complete.
# Flips to 503 during shutdown drain with reason="draining".
GET {{baseUrl}}/ready

###############################################################################
# Catalog probes
###############################################################################

### Model catalog (OpenAI-compatible). Per FR-PR-12 this does NOT enumerate presets.
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/models

### Voice catalog (FR-VS-06). Returns seeds + CRUD voices.
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/tts/voices

###############################################################################
# Basic synthesis with the default preset
#
# When `preset` is omitted, the server resolves `TTS_DEFAULT_PRESET` (ships
# as "balanced"). Response always carries `X-Preset-Effective`; the rich
# endpoint also carries `X-Provider`, `X-Model`, `X-Device`, `X-Dtype`,
# `X-Voice-Source`, `X-Voice-Id`, `X-Chunks`, `X-Total-Duration-Ms`.
###############################################################################

### Buffered synthesis (default preset, default response_format=wav)
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/tts/synthesize
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: audio/wav

{
  "input": "Buongiorno, oggi vi racconto una storia.",
  "voice": "gold",
  "stream": false
}
# Expected response headers include:
#   X-Preset-Effective: balanced(max_sentences_per_chunk=2,normalize_db=-20.0,response_format=wav,temperature=0.8,top_p=0.95)

###############################################################################
# Synthesis with an explicit preset
#
# The "quality" preset pins provider="mlx_audio" + model="Qwen/Qwen3-TTS-12Hz-0.6B-Base"
# + language="en" + response_format="flac". Because the rich pipeline only
# emits WAV today (S-033 pending), `response_format` is soft-ignored and
# reported via `X-Preset-Ignored-Knobs`.
###############################################################################

### Quality preset, buffered (audiobook-style chapter)
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/tts/synthesize
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: audio/wav

{
  "input": "Capitolo primo. In una bella giornata di primavera, il sole splendeva alto nel cielo.",
  "voice": "gold",
  "preset": "quality",
  "stream": false
}
# Expected response headers include:
#   X-Preset-Effective: quality(language=en,max_sentences_per_chunk=3,model=Qwen/Qwen3-TTS-12Hz-0.6B-Base,normalize_db=-20.0,provider=mlx_audio,response_format=flac,temperature=0.8,top_p=0.95)
#   X-Preset-Ignored-Knobs: response_format

###############################################################################
# Precedence demo — explicit field overrides preset (BR-10)
#
# We pick the "quality" preset (which pins language="en") and override
# `language="it"` on the request. The resolver logs a WARN line about the
# override and records it in `X-Preset-Effective` so the client sees what
# actually ran.
###############################################################################

### Quality preset + explicit language override (Italian)
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/tts/synthesize
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: audio/wav

{
  "input": "Il 15/04/2026 abbiamo 2 appuntamenti importanti in agenda.",
  "voice": "gold",
  "preset": "quality",
  "language": "it",
  "stream": false
}
# Expected response headers include:
#   X-Preset-Effective: quality(language=it,max_sentences_per_chunk=3,model=Qwen/Qwen3-TTS-12Hz-0.6B-Base,normalize_db=-20.0,provider=mlx_audio,response_format=flac,temperature=0.8,top_p=0.95)
#   X-Preset-Ignored-Knobs: response_format
#
# Server log line:
#   preset override | request_id=... preset=quality field=language explicit='it' preset='en'

###############################################################################
# Unknown preset → 400 preset_unknown (FR-PR-07)
###############################################################################

### Unknown preset name (negative example)
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/tts/synthesize
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: audio/wav

{
  "input": "Test",
  "voice": "gold",
  "preset": "not-a-real-preset"
}
# Expected:
#   400 with envelope { error: { type: "validation_error", code: "preset_unknown", param: "preset",
#                                message: "unknown preset 'not-a-real-preset'; available presets: ['balanced', 'fast', 'quality']" } }
#   X-Error-Code: preset_unknown

###############################################################################
# Voice-cloning roundtrip (S-022 .. S-025)
#
# Three steps: register a voice via multipart POST, synthesize using its id,
# then delete it. The cycle-1 inline `ref_audio` field is GONE — the voice
# store is the only canonical source of reference audio.
#
# Replace ./samples/gold.wav below with a real reference clip (3–10s mono
# WAV @ 24kHz works well; see README "Voice map").
###############################################################################

### Step 1 — register a cloned voice (multipart)
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/tts/voices
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=BOUNDARY

--BOUNDARY
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="metadata"
Content-Type: application/json

{"id":"voice_demo","transcript":"Ciao, questa è una voce di riferimento.","language":"Italian","number_lang":"it","consent_acknowledged":true,"temperature":0.8,"top_p":0.95,"target_db":-20.0,"max_sentences_per_chunk":2}
--BOUNDARY
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="audio"; filename="gold.wav"
Content-Type: audio/wav

< ./samples/gold.wav
--BOUNDARY--

### Step 2 — synthesize using the registered id
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/tts/synthesize
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: audio/wav

{
  "input": "Benvenuti a questo episodio sperimentale.",
  "voice": "voice_demo",
  "stream": false
}

### Step 3 — fetch the stored reference audio back (FR-VS-07b)
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/tts/voices/voice_demo/audio
# Response carries X-Content-Sha256, X-Voice-Source, X-Voice-Id.

### Step 4 — delete the voice (FR-VS-09)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/v1/tts/voices/voice_demo

###############################################################################
# OpenAI-compatible /v1/audio/speech
#
# Uses TTS_DEFAULT_PRESET on the server side (no `preset` field on the
# OpenAI shape). The response is byte-identical to OpenAI's contract —
# rich-only headers (`X-Provider`, `X-Model`, `X-Device`, `X-Dtype`,
# `X-Voice-Source`, `X-Voice-Id`, `X-Chunks`, `X-Total-Duration-Ms`,
# `X-Preset-Effective`, `X-Preset-Ignored-Knobs`) are stripped.
###############################################################################

### OpenAI adapter — buffered (Italian narration)
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/audio/speech
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: audio/wav

{
  "model": "Qwen/Qwen3-TTS-12Hz-0.6B-Base",
  "provider": "mlx_audio",
  "voice": "gold",
  "input": "Il 15/04/2026 abbiamo 2 appuntamenti.",
  "response_format": "wav"
}
# Expected response headers: X-Request-ID only (rich-only headers stripped).

###############################################################################
# Negative examples — error envelopes (HF-3 messaging)
###############################################################################

### Wrong "provider" value (model family used as provider) — HF-3 error guidance
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/tts/synthesize
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: audio/wav

{
  "input": "Test",
  "voice": "gold",
  "provider": "qwen"
}
# Expected:
#   400 with envelope { error: { type: "validation_error", code: "invalid_parameter", param: "provider",
#                                message: "provider 'qwen' is not supported. Valid providers: mlx_audio, voxtral, vllm-omni.
#                                          Note: 'qwen' refers to a model family, not a provider — use provider='mlx_audio'
#                                          with the desired model (e.g. model='Qwen/Qwen3-TTS-12Hz-0.6B-Base')." } }
#   X-Error-Code: invalid_parameter

### Missing voice (and the active preset does not supply one) → voice_required
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/tts/synthesize
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: audio/wav

{
  "input": "Test senza voce."
}
# Expected:
#   400 with envelope { error: { type: "validation_error", code: "voice_required", param: "voice" } }
#   X-Error-Code: voice_required
#
# Tip: a custom preset that sets `defaults.voice` lets clients omit `voice`
# on the request (HF-2 / FR-PR-03). See README "Audio presets" for the
# `audiobook_it` example.

###############################################################################
# 501-stub endpoints (URL-stable, kept for OpenAI SDK probing)
###############################################################################

### Transcriptions stub
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/audio/transcriptions

### Translations stub
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/audio/translations

### Chat completions stub
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{"model": "gpt-4o-mini", "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "Hello"}]}

### Realtime sessions stub
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/realtime/sessions
